---
# SumelaOS per-developer overrides (PERSONAL — never committed).
#
# Copy this file to `.sumela/local.md` (gitignored) to set YOUR own preferences
# without changing the team-wide project config in AGENTS.md:
#
#   cp .sumela/local.md.example .sumela/local.md
#
# Only the keys listed below — interaction_language and domains — are honored.
# Anything else is ignored.

# Interaction language — the language the agent talks to YOU in (explanations,
# questions, status, the Context Manifest header). Overrides AGENTS.md Section 2's
# project default for your clone only.
interaction_language: English

# Domains — the business domain(s) YOU work in (comma-separated). The agent loads the
# matching domain rules from .sumela/rules/domains/ in ADDITION to phase + stack rules.
# Must be names from the project taxonomy in RULE_REGISTRY.md <domain_scopes>; an
# unknown value is warned-and-skipped, never fatal. Leave blank if you don't work in a
# specific domain. Example:
# domains: Card, Payments
---

<!--
  Why only interaction_language and domains?

  Code NAMING and code DOCUMENTATION languages are deliberately NOT overridable
  here — they must stay consistent across the whole team, so they live only in
  AGENTS.md Section 2 (committed, team-wide). This file changes how the agent
  speaks to you, never what lands in the shared codebase.

  `domains` is per-developer because WHICH domain you work in is personal — but the
  domain TAXONOMY (valid names) and the domain RULES are team-wide and tracked
  (RULE_REGISTRY.md <domain_scopes> + .sumela/rules/domains/). Setting your domain
  here just tells the agent which of those tracked rule sets to load for you.
-->
